text: welcome to Southwest Halloween party an
annual celebration of the airline's
exuberant employees and its zany culture
this year Gary Kelly's dressed as Woody
from Toy Story in previous years he was
Gene Simmons from the rock band Kiss and
Edna from the musical Hairspray he's
also the chief executive behind the
wockii masks Southwest is serious about
its business as it prepares to celebrate
its 40th anniversary next year the
airline is cementing its position as the
largest carrier of domestic passengers
and in September it announced that it
was going to buy airtran for 1.4 billion
dollars the deal will open up Atlanta as
well as expand its presence in New York
and Washington DC but the merger comes
at a pivotal moment for Southwest some
analysts fear it is slowly turning into
a traditional airline and many Southwest
workers say they worried that the
airline's distinctive culture could be
diluted once 8,000 new employees come on
board the company is cultivated it's
irreverent culture carefully and it
recognizes it as a key part of its
competitive advantage last year out of
90,000 applications it received
Southwest hired just 800 people making
it tougher to get a job there than it is
to be accepted into Harvard but a
Southwest expands will it be able to
keep its promise of affordable and
on-time service with first-class legroom
great cocktails for everyone and a
schedule you could depend on
today southwest boasts an eighty-six
percent on-time arrival status which is
just above the industry average but
lagging behind united and continental
meanwhile Southwest continues to compete
with low prices although some experts
point out that the low fare carrier does
not always offer the lowest fares on
every route it serves the average
round-trip ticket on Southwest is 260
dollars that's about eighty dollars
below the industry average as other
airline's moved to charge passengers for
services that were once free Southwest
cents an opportunity to showcase its
difference again bucking the trend
Southwest made its bags fly free policy
a centerpiece of a recent advertising
and marketing campaign so can the
marriage of southwest and airtran
